1
00:00:04,342 --> 00:00:06,459
The basis of what
I was saying was,

2
00:00:06,459 --> 00:00:09,434
it’s built upon 
the concept of perspective.

3
00:00:09,727 --> 00:00:13,307
[Socrates, Castro and the King of India]

4
00:00:13,538 --> 00:00:16,261
When Freud was asked,

5
00:00:16,261 --> 00:00:19,662
“What is the purpose
of psychoanalysis?”

6
00:00:20,553 --> 00:00:24,638
He said—
and remember, “psycho” means “soul”,

7
00:00:25,946 --> 00:00:28,782
so we can say “soul analysis”—

8
00:00:28,782 --> 00:00:32,572
and he said,
“To convert neurotic suffering

9
00:00:32,618 --> 00:00:35,180
into ordinary suffering.”

10
00:00:35,563 --> 00:00:37,619
People thought
he was going to say,

11
00:00:37,619 --> 00:00:40,542
“To make people happy, 
that’s the purpose.

12
00:00:40,542 --> 00:00:42,783
When you undergo
this type of analysis,

13
00:00:42,783 --> 00:00:45,068
you’ll come out a happy person.”

14
00:00:45,068 --> 00:00:47,308
That’s what they thought, 
but that’s not what he said,

15
00:00:47,308 --> 00:00:51,526
he said, “Oh, to convert neurotic suffering
into ordinary suffering.”

16
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:54,373
It’s a little bit of a clever repartee,

17
00:00:54,373 --> 00:00:58,880
but there’s something 
to be said about that.

18
00:00:59,696 --> 00:01:07,015
So what I was suggesting, 
by observation,

19
00:01:09,860 --> 00:01:13,404
we see: the cause of the suffering 
of Vraja-gopīs

20
00:01:13,634 --> 00:01:17,223
and others
is separation from Kṛṣṇa—

21
00:01:17,484 --> 00:01:20,481
as given in the Gopī-gītā,

22
00:01:20,620 --> 00:01:23,500
those ślokas, 
“Tava kathāmṛtaḿ tapta-jīvanaḿ” 
etc. [SB: 10.31.9]

23
00:01:25,452 --> 00:01:26,994
Then we hear in the Bhāgavatam,

24
00:01:26,994 --> 00:01:30,846
bhayaḿ dvitīyābhiniveśataḥ syād

25
00:01:30,846 --> 00:01:34,307
īśād apetasya viparyayo ’smṛtiḥ 
[SB: 11.2.37].

26
00:01:34,307 --> 00:01:36,582
Here we want to say 
“forgetfulness”,

27
00:01:36,582 --> 00:01:40,297
but the cause is separation.

28
00:01:40,297 --> 00:01:43,023
I’m applying it to this also,
and saying

29
00:01:43,238 --> 00:01:47,942
that the real cause of
our present suffering

30
00:01:47,942 --> 00:01:50,502
is separation from Kṛṣṇa.

31
00:01:50,502 --> 00:01:54,300
But this is one type, 
that’s another type,

32
00:01:56,314 --> 00:02:03,702
so both can be a starting point.

33
00:02:03,702 --> 00:02:06,222
So, when we read in the Gītā

34
00:02:06,222 --> 00:02:09,139
—but it’s qualified by the word sukṛti—
it’s saying,

35
00:02:09,139 --> 00:02:13,875
people in different types 
of distressed conditions

36
00:02:13,875 --> 00:02:16,900
(I’ll say it that way 
for the sake of this talk),

37
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:22,179
if they have the sukṛti—
it doesn’t say everybody,

38
00:02:22,179 --> 00:02:25,625
but it says, janāḥ sukṛtino ’rjuna 
[Bg: 7.16],

39
00:02:25,625 --> 00:02:29,262
those who have sufficient sukṛti,

40
00:02:29,262 --> 00:02:32,096
when they’re 
in these circumstances,

41
00:02:32,096 --> 00:02:40,073
it may be a catalyst for 
coming in connection, spiritual search.

42
00:02:40,385 --> 00:02:42,581
Not everybody.

43
00:02:42,581 --> 00:02:45,300
Everyone is suffering 
in different ways,

44
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:48,185
but why is it, one person ...?

45
00:02:48,737 --> 00:02:51,275
Like Prabhupād says in one place, 
when someone

46
00:02:51,275 --> 00:02:56,063
realises that the complexity
of material life

47
00:02:56,124 --> 00:02:59,587
is a constant source of perplexity, 
bewilderment,

48
00:02:59,587 --> 00:03:04,176
confusion, and anxiety, 
it behooves such a person

49
00:03:04,176 --> 00:03:07,482
to approach a spiritual master.

50
00:03:07,867 --> 00:03:10,570
But not everybody does that.

51
00:03:10,570 --> 00:03:12,797
So the key word there is sukṛti.

52
00:03:12,797 --> 00:03:15,300
Those of sufficient sukṛti,

53
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:18,608
when they find themselves
in some completely

54
00:03:18,608 --> 00:03:23,389
distressing circumstance 
or depression …

55
00:03:24,233 --> 00:03:31,223
Vedavyās’s depression led him 
to dive deep into Reality.

56
00:03:31,238 --> 00:03:33,735
Of course, that’s a high example,
Vedavyās.

57
00:03:33,735 --> 00:03:36,809
But someone within this world:
it may,

58
00:03:36,809 --> 00:03:38,942
but it may be temporary also.

59
00:03:38,942 --> 00:03:42,541
We hear of śmaśāna vairāgya:

60
00:03:42,541 --> 00:03:48,843
the renunciation at the funeral pyre.

61
00:03:50,717 --> 00:03:54,623
People go to a funeral, 
and momentarily they’re thinking,

62
00:03:54,623 --> 00:03:58,660
I heard some news today,
some horrible news we hear

63
00:03:58,969 --> 00:04:03,268
about some children dying somewhere, 
or some other people,

64
00:04:03,484 --> 00:04:13,206
and then we may think,
“What is this world? It’s so brutal.”

65
00:04:13,690 --> 00:04:16,726
Prabhupād would sometimes
quote Saraswatī Ṭhākur

66
00:04:16,726 --> 00:04:20,142
saying, 
“It’s not a place fit for gentlemen”,

67
00:04:20,142 --> 00:04:24,789
and these different feelings
may come to us.

68
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:29,301
But then they leave easily, also.

69
00:04:30,054 --> 00:04:32,150
So, again in the Gītā 
Kṛṣṇa’s saying,

70
00:04:32,150 --> 00:04:37,828
janma-mṛtyu-jarā-vyādhi-
duḥkha-doṣānudarśanam
[Bg: 13.9],

71
00:04:38,352 --> 00:04:42,617
if you’ve got the right darshan, 
perspective,

72
00:04:42,617 --> 00:04:46,222
of where you are in the world,

73
00:04:46,559 --> 00:04:51,299
then you’ll realise that suffering, birth, 
death, old age, and disease,

74
00:04:51,299 --> 00:04:54,629
these are things
that are inescapable,

75
00:04:54,629 --> 00:04:57,871
and you’re gonna 
have to deal with them

76
00:04:57,871 --> 00:05:02,454
whether you’re in Kṛṣṇa consciousness 
or not.

77
00:05:03,515 --> 00:05:09,195
As Guru Mahārāj defined “śūdra”,

78
00:05:09,243 --> 00:05:15,354
in relation to the Rāmachandra pastime
of beheading śūdraka,

79
00:05:15,425 --> 00:05:24,537
he said, “’Śūdra’, by definition, means 
‘one who wails or laments’.”

80
00:05:24,608 --> 00:05:26,689
That’s what it literally means.

81
00:05:26,689 --> 00:05:34,471
Śūdra, ‘who’s crying out in agony, 
anxiety, wailing, lamenting’.

82
00:05:34,612 --> 00:05:35,866
Why?

83
00:05:35,897 --> 00:05:38,441
Guru Mahārāj, his explanation was, 
he said,

84
00:05:38,441 --> 00:05:42,177
“One who accepts this life as all in all,

85
00:05:42,177 --> 00:05:44,604
this world as all in all,

86
00:05:44,604 --> 00:05:47,486
he will have to lament.”

87
00:05:47,716 --> 00:05:52,431
That’s why Śukadev—
again, very strong language—

88
00:05:52,492 --> 00:05:56,742
is telling Parīkṣit Mahārāj 
near the end of the Bhāgavatam,

89
00:05:57,126 --> 00:06:03,365
tvaḿ tu rājan mariṣyeti
paśu-buddhim imāḿ jahi
[SB: 12.5.2]

90
00:06:03,444 --> 00:06:06,549
I mean it almost sounds insulting,

91
00:06:06,608 --> 00:06:11,148
he’s saying, 
“To think that you will die is paśu-buddhi.

92
00:06:11,148 --> 00:06:14,769
Animals think they will die.”

93
00:06:14,998 --> 00:06:19,117
He’s saying, a spiritually realised
advanced person,

94
00:06:19,117 --> 00:06:21,171
he won’t think like that.

95
00:06:21,233 --> 00:06:25,959
Dhīras tatra na muhyati [Bg: 2.13]— 
he won’t be bewildered by this.

96
00:06:26,114 --> 00:06:32,355
Socrates,
“Bring the Hemlock! Big glass!”

97
00:06:33,321 --> 00:06:36,312
Saying that, 
“My body will be finished,

98
00:06:36,312 --> 00:06:38,104
but I won’t be.”
He knew that.

99
00:06:38,119 --> 00:06:44,095
Fidel Castro wrote some letters 
in the 1950s

100
00:06:44,095 --> 00:06:49,488
—they discovered these kind of
like spiritual letters he wrote—

101
00:06:49,503 --> 00:06:53,106
and, I’m paraphrasing,
but he practically said,

102
00:06:53,106 --> 00:06:56,725
“Once you realise that 
you’re not your material body,

103
00:06:56,725 --> 00:06:58,681
but that you’re a spiritual being,

104
00:06:58,681 --> 00:07:03,398
you’re not afraid of dying
for the revolution, etc.”

105
00:07:03,398 --> 00:07:07,747
Even he could understand that, 
on some level.

106
00:07:07,747 --> 00:07:11,000
Socrates, Fidel Castro.

107
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:15,829
That’s why Mahāprabhu
was telling Sanātan,

108
00:07:15,829 --> 00:07:20,105
“To offer your body?
That won’t get you Kṛṣṇa.”

